      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GLAMOUR ZONE (8) comes off a moderate effort last start, finishing fourth at this track over 390m behind Pilot Prince (22.58). Has claims if she runs up to expectations. DIMORA PATCH (3) has an honest record despite remaining a maiden and overdue for a win, having placed six of 16 career runs. Although yet to win tends to go well here. Form from his last run is proving strong. Key player if finds best. GOTHAM SORCERESS (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Warragul behind Waltzing Blaster (23.22) in a Maiden. Turned chasing the leaders but kept coming. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Expected to be in this for a long way. PAW XELA (2) is a last-start placegetter who is in the mix again.",
